# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Compiler Phases Block Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    SRC["Source Program<br/>(.c file)"] --> LEX["Lexical Analyzer<br/>(Scanner)"]
    LEX -->|Token Stream| SYN["Syntax Analyzer<br/>(Parser)"]
    SYN -->|Parse Tree| SEM["Semantic Analyzer"]
    SEM -->|Annotated Tree| ICG["Intermediate Code Gen"]
    ICG --> OPT["Optimizer"]
    OPT --> TCG["Target Code Gen"]
    TCG --> ASM["Target Code<br/>(Assembly / Machine)"]
    LEX -.-> ST1[("Symbol Table")]
    SYN -.-> ST1
    SEM -.-> ST1
```

## 4.2 Lexical Analyzer Internal Workflow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    START([Start: Open input file]) --> READ[Read next character ch]
    READ --> WS{Is ch whitespace?}
    WS -->|Yes, skip| READ
    WS -->|No| COMM{ch == '/' ?}
    COMM -->|Yes| CHECKLA{Lookahead next char}
    CHECKLA -->|'/' single-line| SKIP1[Skip until newline]
    CHECKLA -->|'*' multi-line| SKIP2[Skip until star-slash]
    CHECKLA -->|No, genuine operator| OP1[Emit OPERATOR /]
    SKIP1 --> READ
    SKIP2 --> READ
    OP1 --> READ
    COMM -->|No| STR{ch == '"' ?}
    STR -->|Yes| SCANSTR[Read until next quote, emit STRING]
    STR -->|No| ALPHA{isalpha or _ ?}
    ALPHA -->|Yes| BUFID[Buffer until non-alphanumeric]
    BUFID --> KW{isKeyword?}
    KW -->|Yes| EMITKW[Emit KEYWORD]
    KW -->|No| EMITID[Emit IDENTIFIER]
    EMITKW --> READ
    EMITID --> READ
    SCANSTR --> READ
    ALPHA -->|No| DIG{isdigit ?}
    DIG -->|Yes| BUFNUM[Buffer digits and one dot]
    BUFNUM --> EMITNUM[Emit NUMBER]
    EMITNUM --> READ
    DIG -->|No| OP2{Operator symbol?}
    OP2 -->|Yes| PEEK[Peek next char for 2-char op]
    PEEK --> EMITOP[Emit OPERATOR]
    EMITOP --> READ
    OP2 -->|No| PUNC{Punctuator?}
    PUNC -->|Yes| EMITPUNC[Emit SYMBOL]
    EMITPUNC --> READ
    PUNC -->|No| ERR[Emit LEXICAL ERROR]
    ERR --> READ
    READ -->|EOF| STOP([End: Close file])
```

## 4.3 Token Classification Hierarchy

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    T[Token Stream Output] --> K1[KEYWORD]
    T --> K2[IDENTIFIER]
    T --> K3[NUMBER]
    T --> K4[OPERATOR]
    T --> K5[SYMBOL]
    T --> K6[STRING]
    T --> K7[PREPROCESSOR]
    T --> K8[LEXICAL ERROR]

    K4 --> K4a[Arithmetic: + - * / %]
    K4 --> K4b[Relational: == != < > <= >=]
    K4 --> K4c[Logical: && || !]
    K4 --> K4d[Bitwise: & \| ^ ~ << >>]
    K4 --> K4e[Assignment: = += -= *= /= %=]
    K4 --> K4f[Increment / Decrement: ++ --]

    K3 --> K3a[Integer: 0-9 digits]
    K3 --> K3b[Floating: digits.digits]
    K3 --> K3c[Exponent: digits.digits e digits]
```

## 4.4 Symbol Table Interaction

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    LEX[Lexical Analyzer] -->|insert / lookup| ST[("Symbol Table<br/>id --> attributes")]
    ST -->|pointer| TOK[Token Attribute Field]
    SYN[Syntax Analyzer] -->|lookup| ST
    SEM[Semantic Analyzer] -->|update type info| ST
    CG[Code Generator] -->|fetch address| ST
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU Diagram Interpretation Tip:** When asked in the exam to *"draw the block diagram of a compiler"*, the symbol table is shown as a **separate vertical data structure** on the side that **all phases (lexical, syntax, semantic, code generation) access** — not as a sequential phase. This is a frequently asked **3-mark question**.

