# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. `[KTU University Exam – May 2024, PCCSL607 Model]`
**Define a lexical analyzer. What are its input and output?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

A **lexical analyzer** is the first phase of a compiler that performs lexical analysis. It reads the source program as a stream of characters, removes white spaces and comments, and groups the remaining characters into meaningful sequences called **lexemes**, each of which corresponds to a **token**.

- **Input:** Source program (raw character stream from a `.c` file).
- **Output:** Stream of tokens in the form $\langle \text{token-name}, \text{attribute-value} \rangle$ which is sent to the syntax analyzer.

Secondary outputs include updated **symbol table** entries and **line numbers** for error reporting.

---

### Q2. `[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023, PCCSL607 Model]`
**Differentiate between a Token, a Lexeme, and a Pattern with suitable examples.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

| Term | Meaning | Example for `int count = 5;` |
|---|---|---|
| **Token** | A classification / category of lexemes | `<KEYWORD>`, `<IDENTIFIER>`, `<NUMBER>` |
| **Lexeme** | The actual character sequence matched | `int`, `count`, `5` |
| **Pattern** | The rule describing all lexemes of a token | `[A-Za-z\_][A-Za-z0-9\_]*` for identifiers |

The pattern is what the lexer **searches for**, the lexeme is **what it actually finds**, and the token is the **label it assigns**.

---

## 5.2 Part B Questions (14 Marks Each — Internal Choice)

### `Q3. Question A (14 Marks)` `[KTU University Exam – Jul 2024, PCCSL607]`

**(a)** Explain the different **roles and functions** of a lexical analyzer in a compiler. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Design and implement a **C program** to recognize the following token categories from an input file: **keywords, identifiers, numbers, operators, and special symbols**. The program must skip white spaces (` `, `\t`, `\n`) and both single-line (`//`) and multi-line (`/* */`) comments. **(7 marks)**

### Model Solution

**(a) Roles and Functions of a Lexical Analyzer (7 marks):**

1. **Tokenization** — Convert character stream into token stream.
2. **White-space and comment removal** — Discard formatting characters that carry no semantic meaning.
3. **Symbol table management** — Insert and lookup identifiers in the symbol table.
4. **Line number counting** — Maintain counters for accurate error messages.
5. **Error reporting** — Detect illegal characters and report them with line/column numbers.
6. **Constant folding at lexical level** — Some constants can be pre-computed.
7. **Decoupling input alphabet handling** — Isolates OS/file encoding issues from the parser.

**(b) C Program (7 marks):**

The complete C program is the same as listed in **Section 3.1** of these notes. Key code sections that must appear in any model answer for full marks:

```c
